# PickerQuant UI requirements

Before modifying frontend code:

1. Read design-system/MASTER.md.
2. Read the relevant design-system/pages/[page].md file.
3. Preserve existing backend contracts, calculations and financial data.
4. Never remove functionality merely to simplify the interface.
5. Preserve Buy, Hold and Sell percentages and semantic colors.
6. Prefer shared components and tokens over page-specific styling.
7. Avoid large empty spaces, oversized cards and low-contrast text.
8. Keep tables and analytical information compact and readable.
9. Every changed page must support desktop, laptop and mobile layouts.
10. Run lint, type checking, tests and production build after changes.---
